         Mend Companion is pointless when using a summoned pet.  But, when used in conjunction with a dire pet that has 5k+ hit points, the value of this skill becomes more apparent.</P><P>Pet Hold Skill is VERY useful for pulling mobs, especially caster mobs, from long distances where you have to run back to where your pet is parked.  This skill is pretty much invaluable when soloing indoors with a pet.  Yeah the pet not attacking mezzed mobs change may seem like it devalues this skill, but in reality it does not.  The change made recently to pets regarding mezzed mobs actually makes your pet more valuable, and does not degrade any of our skills.</P><P>Life Burn is a great skill.  Smaller guilds can make tremendous use of 4k unresistable damage to mobs like Kunark dragons and Epic mobs.  Granted, for larger and more powerful guilds, this skill becomes less useful.. mobs with 150k+ hit points don't really drop any faster if a few necros are Life Burning it.  Yes, it should be able to crit.. this is the flaw in the Life Burn skill.  As a side note on Life Burn, by using a self rune and harmshield you can avoid any unwanted attention from a mob after you Burn it.</P><P>And as Sally mentioned, there are a lot of places and situations where either AE undead mez -or- AE fear would be incredibly useful.  However, the actual cast time of these skills makes them not so useful in a situation where you might be using these skills to their full potential.</P><P>As for Arch skills, i would put points into Expertise before Channeling.  Never fizzling FD and Harmshield is UBER and will save your LIFE.  As it is, i channel very well against most anything that i would expect to stand up to for more than several seconds. Sure it would be nice to channel a little more, and maybe its just me, but fizzles really piss me off.</P><P>Oh, and i don't really think Mental Clarity is that useful to us. I do like your idea for added hit point regen though, would be nice to have that as an option instead of MC.</P><P>Other than the above points, i mostly agree with what you are saying.  But, like Sally said: For VI to take it seriously, it has to be PERFECT and make sense to, and be endorsed by, the majority of us Necros.  Don't take our criticism as flaming. </P><P>Vtyn<BR>Warlock<BR>Heaven and Earth</P><P> <a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height="15" width="15" border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top of Page"></a></font></td>
