        <hr noshade size="2" color="#545A7D">
        
         I took some of the post I made in general and posted it here since I think it applies.  Essentially, I think VI needs to take a second look at our AA abilities.</P><P>For existing abilities:<BR>- Mend companion: this skill needs a faster refresh rate. 2+ hours is just ludicrous for complete heal on a pet. I'd say lower this to 30 minutes, or at least have the option of lowering the recast time by putting multiple levels (3/6/9) on this skill; not unbalancing at all and would make this skill remotely worth having.<BR>- Lifeburn: I really think VI went overboard when they designed the limitations/drawbacks for this ability, especially when compared to manaburn. I don't want to get into a comparison or turn it into a wizards vs. necro bitch, but manaburn has ways in which its limitation (leaving the wizard with no mana) can easily be negated (mod rods for one). The fact that the necro is dropped to 1 health has a twofold effect of leaving the necro vulnerable to easy death to to AE and such along with insta super agro. There really is no way to overcome this either, as even having manaskin doesn't avoid the low health agro problems.  Against any boss mob raid, manaskin or rune won't even come close to saving you; when I've died to this, there isn't even enough time to toss up harmshield.<BR>- Dead Mesmerization: Fix this broken ability already! I recall a raid in Akheva where a bad pull could have been brought under control had this skill actually worked as advertised. I can't believe this has gotten such a low priority that its still broken.<BR>- Mass Group Buff: I think its a bit silly that it costs 9 AA points to MGB the one group spell necros have which also happens to be a nonpurchaseable, rare spell.</P><P>Suggestions/additions:<BR>- As 'masters of the undead', I believe necs got a raw deal in that we have no AA skills to enhance our offensive abilities (nukes, etc) vs. the undead. Paladins have Slay Undead which allows them to do disgusting crits to undead (I frequently see 3k-4k hits on undead mobs by guild paladins with this skill). What about a similar ability for us when we use our undead nukes?</P><P>The entire concept of necros becoming liches was something that could have been tapped into with AA abilities. How about a skill which allows the necro to assume lich form with either limitless or near limitless duration which remains while zoning? This lich form could have the bonus of being stackable with clarity perhaps.</P><P>Some spells we have allow us to control our bodies in certain ways. example; that we don't need to breathe (breath of the dead). I see potential for an AA skill there. </P><P>I think there is enormous roleplaying potential with AA abilities which is completely going to waste for us. When I look at the excitement some other classes have over their AA skills, I get a bit depressed to think that spell casting mastery 3 and innate invis undead is about the best it gets for us.  We need more AA abilities that expand upon spells and skills we already have, not fluf abilities which are conveniences at best.</P><P>=-=-=-=-=-=-=<BR>Aildrik T'Quetzl<BR>"The more fear you make, the more loot you take"<BR>- Lex Luthar, Superman IV<a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height="15" width="15" border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top of Page"></a></font></td>
